      <textAnnotation id="sid-5142449E-CE8F-4199-A6C9-1C1383926255" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Process Tower: Procure To Pay
Process Group: Procure Materials and Services (Direct &amp; Indirect)
Process: PM-040-230 Collect Supplier Performance Data
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-A278278E-5D61-45E2-8A9F-BBE107F499C9" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>SOW's defined, EPIC program, technical specs, etc.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-65AF39F8-32C2-49EB-B07C-875E6B1FED75" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Data like Risk, sustainability, financial health, manufacturing, quality, etc.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-B77DD5C8-07DB-42AC-8E5E-57022178A567" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>includes data from sources like- 
*SIC- Supplier Survey Tool
*Supplier Publicity and Confidentiality Program
*The Grid
*Global Supply Chain Sustainability</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-C67EFB13-ECBD-44EF-AA80-218C807F8694" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>L3 Description-
Quantitative and qualitative supplier data may be obtained from the database of receipts, inspections, audits, etc. Other informational database should be referenced, as well as testimonies of company employees involved with the purchasing relationship. </text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-420E87E9-EB75-4E39-A270-398F931080D4" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Boundary Apps:​

Performance management  online SRC, theGrid, Supplier 360 (SDM, SAM),  3rd parties (SRS, Security Scorecard)​

Social responsibility deliverables (Bapp: Graphite, suppliersoft, email)​

Supplier training (Bapp: docebo)​.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-FC8FBCFD-575A-4A44-AC27-4CB0767722E9" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Reporting:​

Supplier Mgmt Overivew (summary level) ​

Analytics/Reporting based on ECA data.  No direct S4 connection.​

Segmentation drives the level of performance and actions to manage supplier​

               -  Supplier Hierarchy summary - global/children, associated contract(s), spends/commits, segmentation level, contacts, contract owner​

               -  Contract Overview - contractID, contract name, amendments, owners, committs/paid against, expiry​

               -  Spends breakdown by TCOO / sourcing category;  high level sourcing org​

               -  Responsibility &amp; Risk:  deliverables assigned, criteria, and status​

               -  Supplier report card:  line items, owners, due dates, status, comments, quality​

               -  Supplier improvement plans (includes Quality):  SOR is TBD​</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-E23B38FA-25DC-4BAB-BF08-30117F5DFA0C" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Reporting:​

Supplier Performance Operational Details/KPIs  (driven by individual L3 processes across functions).   ​

Ex:   Contract process KPIs, delivery performance, PO commit/decommit, Quality process controls/audits/remediation      ​

Includes both standard S4 report to call operational supplier data  and  ECA based dashboards​</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-96B01D22-8899-47DA-982C-9C6BA8E8DF10" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform the process steward Dhanwantry, Kalyan R &lt;kalyan.r.dhanwantry@intel.com&gt; and BPM Champions D'Elia, Traci &lt;traci.delia@intel.com&gt;,Newman, Jennifer &lt;jennifer.newman@intel.com&gt;of any design changes that occur within the flow moving forward. This will enable us to reflect those changes in the BIC and WIKI business process documentation.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
